	    <img SRC="zeus_small2.gif" ALT="ZEUS" height=77 width=77 align=Right>
	    <h1 align=center><font color=black>tLite Home page</font></h1>
	  </td></tr>
    </table>
    <br> <br>
    The tLite library is a collection of tracking related analysis tools.<br>
    New analysis strategies that use the improved spatial resolution of the MVD
can be implemented with these tools.
    <br><br>
    <table border=0 cellspacing=0 width="100%">
	<tr>
	  <td align=left>
	    <strong>Packages:</strong>
	    <ul> 
	      <li> VxLite:<br>
		lightweight vertexing package
		<ul>
		  <li> <a href="vxlite.html">vxlitefit</a> (vertex fit) 
		  <li> <a href="vxlite.html">vxlitefitcov</a> (vertex fit returning the errors on the improved track parameters)
		  <li> <a href="vxlite.html">vxlitefitit</a> (iterated vertex fit)
		  <li> <a href="vxlite.html">vxlitefititcstr</a> (constraining vertex fit)
		  <li> <a href="daf.html">vxlitedaffit</a> (vertex fit with smooth outlier removal)
		</ul>
	      <li> DCA:<br>
		distance of closest approach of two helices or a helix and a point
		<ul>
		  <li> <a href="dca.html">tlidca</a> (distance of closest approach)
		  <li> <a href="dca.html">tlidcav</a> (distance of closest approach)
		  <li> <a href="dcapoint.html">tlidcapoint</a> (distance from space point)
		</ul>
	      <li> helix utility functions:
		<ul>
		  <li> <a href="helix.html">tliphel</a> (four momentum and its covariance matrix from a helix)
		  <li> <a href="helix.html">tlipnewpar</a> (four momentum from vertex constrained track parameters)
		</ul>
	      <li> kinematic Fits: 
		<ul>
		  <li> <a href="fitm.html">tlifitm</a> (mass constraint fit)
		</ul>
	      <li> MC tools:
		<ul>
		  <li> <a href="tliPattern.html">tliPattern</a>(analysis of complex decay chains)
		  <li> <a href="tliPartTab.html">tliPartTab</a>(interface to the ZEUS particle table)
		</ul>
	    </ul><br>
	    <stronG>Example:</strong><br>
	    <a href="zuanal.fpp">Some example code</a> using most of the described functions.
	    <br><br>
	    <strong>Usage:</strong><br>
	    Since ZEUS release v2005a.1 the tLite library is included into the linking of any eaze job. Therefore, no modifications are required in your makefiles.
<!--	    For linking include the following lines in your Makefile.postamble:<br>
	    USERLIBS += -L/opt/products/CLHEP/1.8.2/lib -lCLHEP<br>
	    USERLIBS += -L/data/zenith217a/stadie/tlite/lib/${ZARCH_TYPE} -ltlite-->
	    <br><br>
	    <strong>Other useful functions (vcrecon):</strong><br>
	    <ul>
	      <li> vcreref (change reference point for helix parameters). It is described in this <a href="hartner.ps.gz">talk</a> on page 36.
	      <li> <a href="vmcu.ps.gz">vmcu</a> (matches tracks and MC particles) 
	    </ul>
	  </td>
	  <td align=left>
	    <img src="k0.png" align=MIDDLE alt="K0s decay">   
	  </td></tr>
